Consolidate to single Next.js server with full API routes

Migrated entire Python backend into Next.js API Route Handlers:
- Ported Gemini provider, pipeline, caption formatter, compliance scorer, LMS exporter to TypeScript
- Created 28 API route handlers matching all previous FastAPI endpoints
- Added server-side infrastructure (auth, supabase service role, rate limiting, config)
- Frontend api.ts now uses relative /api/* URLs (no separate backend needed)
- Added COOP/COEP headers for ffmpeg.wasm SharedArrayBuffer support
- Added maxDuration=300 for Vercel Pro serverless function timeouts
- Added GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS_JSON env var support for serverless deployments
- Simplified Gemini transcription to segment-level confidence (fixes JSON overflow on long lectures)
- All Gemini calls use responseMimeType: application/json for reliable output
- Removed output:standalone (not needed for Vercel)
- Single `npm run dev` now runs everything on localhost:3000
